        "text_color_2": "#bfbfbf",
        "text_color_3": "#8a8a8a",
        "border_color": "#ffffff14",
        "idea_eyebrow": "— The idea behind RD1 —",
        "idea_title": "<strong>Designed for your </strong><em><strong>whole day.</strong></em>",
        "idea_subtext": "<p>RD1 is lightweight and low-profile, which is designed so you can speak naturally, breathe easily, commute, train at the gym, and go about your normal life without any issues.Think of it as the daytime counterpart to your Reviv mouthguard (R1/R2/R3) appliance. Day and night together means consistent, compounding progress.<br/><br/>Day and night. Together, that's when the real progress happens.</p>",
        "day_eyebrow": "— Where you'll wear it —",
        "day_title": "Designed for Your <em>Whole Day</em>",
        "mold_eyebrow": "— How to mold it —",
        "mold_title": "You're wearing this through your whole day. <em>It needs to fit perfectly.</em>",
        "mold_body": "<p>You're talking, training, commuting, going about your day life — RD1 needs to move with you, not against you. That only happens when it's molded specifically to your mouth. Not a generic average. Yours.</p><p>A good fit means it stays in place, feels natural, and you forget it's even there. A poor fit means you'll take it out and stop wearing it altogether.</p><p>Because your bite subtly shifts as your jaw improves over time, we recommend remolding once a week. It takes 10 minutes and keeps RD1 tracking your progress the whole way through.</p>",
        "video_external": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=roBsgSYzcr8",
        "video_link_label": "Watch the RD1 molding video",
        "steps_title": "6 Simple Steps. <em>Perfect Fit.</em>",
        "steps_subtext": "<p>The boil-and-bite process takes under 10 minutes.<br/>Here's exactly how to do it right.</p>",
        "steps_video_external": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8t0ObAOROs8",
        "steps_video_link_label": "Watch the steps video",
        "remold_title": "Remold Once a Week.",
        "remold_body": "<p>RD1 is designed for regular remolding — <strong>once per week is what we recommend.</strong></p><p>Why? Because your bite subtly shifts as your structure improves over time. Weekly remolding ensures RD1 keeps up with your progress and continues to fit perfectly — so it never stops doing its job.</p>",
        "remold_footnote": "If it ever feels loose, tight, or uncomfortable before the week is up — remold it. Your comfort is your signal."
      }
    },
