    "collapsible_content_HA7hTA": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_bdwWYh": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What is RevivDay?",
            "icon": "lightning_bolt",
            "row_content": "<p>RevivDay is a lightweight, discreet daytime mouthguard engineered for comfort and protection. Unlike traditional guards, it’s designed for working, gym, jogging, or social settings.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_b3Aq6U": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How is it different from R1 & R2?",
            "icon": "lightning_bolt",
            "row_content": "<p>RD1 uses the same biomechanics as R1 & R2 but tends to be a bit easier to wear and offers a bit less stretch.  But it is perfect for daytime activities and preventing regression.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_46p3KR": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What if I didn't mold it correctly and it has deformed?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>In cases like this just mold it again.  It is very hard to damage the RD1 since the transparent part is completely remoldable.  It is only when you damage the yellow base that the appliance is truly damaged.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_zVraUA": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I wear it at night?",
            "icon": "lightning_bolt",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes absolutely but it will tend to be a bit less stretch than R1/R2/R3.  Many folks use RD1 as a transition to those other mouthguards as it tends to be easier to start with.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_wYPXBk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Will I get the same results as R1/R2?",
            "icon": "lightning_bolt",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes. RD1 maintains the same benefits, but is best used alongside R1/R2 for 24-hour coverage.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_7ExR9g": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How do I clean RevivDay?",
            "icon": "lightning_bolt",
            "row_content": "<p>Clean with soap and warm water (not boiling). We also recommend using Repod Repod Ultrasonic Cleaner for Dentist-Level Cleaning in just 3 Minutes</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_zHYD8j": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How do I mold it?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p><strong>Watch Video here: </strong><a href=\"https://youtube.com/shorts/8t0ObAOROs8?si=tuxKy0IQ5tGiiJ2D\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://youtube.com/shorts/8t0ObAOROs8?si=tuxKy0IQ5tGiiJ2D\">https://youtube.com/shorts/8t0ObAOROs8?si=tuxKy0IQ5tGiiJ2D</a><strong><br/><br/>Step 1: Boil <br/></strong>Fill a pot with enough water to submerge the RevivDay mouthguard without touching the bottom. Bring the water to a gentle boil.<br/><br/><strong>Step 2: Drop<br/></strong>Turn off the heat and carefully place the mouthguard into the hot water. Let it soak for 60 seconds.<br/><br/><strong>Step 3: Retrieve & Cool<br/></strong>Use a slotted spoon to remove the mouthguard and immediately place it into a bowl of cold water for 3-5 seconds.<br/><br/><strong>Step 4: Mold<br/></strong>Stand in front of a mirror and place RevivDay onto your lower teeth. Ensure your teeth sit in the center of the bite channel (not pressing against the side walls).<br/>- Gently bite down<br/>- Press your fingers against the side walls to shape the fit around your teeth<br/>- Keep it in your mouth for at least 5 minutes for best molding results</p><p><strong>Step 5: Set<br/></strong>After molding, place the mouthguard back in cold water for 5 minutes to solidify the fit.<br/><br/><strong>Step 6: Ready for Use<br/></strong>After you take the appliance out of the cold water it is ready to be used!<br/>Note that the lower teeth will still move a little bit with this process even though you are wearing the RD1 on top of them. And that movement is good.<br/>For this reason you should re-mold your RD1 about once a week to continue to allow the lower teeth to move and upright.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_VrBWRK": {
